body:
@iant has already made this very clear.

The EBNF accepts a wider syntax by design, because it makes the syntax simpler. It's also easier to see the big picture this way - special cases are handled in the prose.

Note that the correct fix would be more complicated than your suggestion because you can have a variadic parameter in the first position (no leading "," in that case), as in:

func f(...T)

If you have a correct suggestion that's just as simple as what we have now, I'm happy to consider it.

Finally, even for a parser it makes sense to accept a wider syntax (and have the restrictions checked separately) because it permits better error handling.
